  "text": "In vitro biochemical synthesis is required to reconstruct cellular functions. Protein-incorporated polymersomes can act as an artificial organelle, performing complex biological processes in vitro [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . As part of our efforts to engineer complex life process, we have demonstrated ATP synthesis from bacteriorhodopsin and F O F 1 -ATP synthase reconstituted polymersomes (abbreviated as BR-ATP synthase-polymersomes) (Figure 6a ) [CITATION_6] .",
